{{ heading('Core colors', '2') }}
<vwc-note connotation="information">
	<p><b>Core color tokens</b> should only be used to construct semantic and pattern design tokens and never used directly in code.</p>
</vwc-note>
{{ heading('Color scales', '3') }}
<p>Vivid:Apps' colors scales provides a range of shades from light to dark, the neutral scale includes white. They are available in both light and dark modes.</p>
<p>The direction of all the core color scales are inverted between modes: the light scale starts at the lightest shade, while the dark scale starts at the darkest. This inversion allows both themes to share the same semantic colour tokens, reducing the need for mode-specific overrides.</p>

<div><b>Neutral color scale</b></div>
